Theodore GESELLE v. UNITED STATES. No. 448. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. March 19, 1931. Ayres, Cowan, McCorkle & Fair and Dempster 0. Potts, all of Wichita, Kan., for appellant. Dan B. Cowie, Asst. U. S. Atty., of Tope- ' ka, Kan., for appellee.

Before LEWIS and McDERMOTT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed March 19, 1931, per stipulation, at costs of appellant.
